## Professional Experience

### Escobedo Group LLP

**Architectural Designer & R&D Software Engineer**
January 2023 – Present

Vertically integrated design-build and fabrication firm delivering panelized construction systems with in-house manufacturing.

**Technical Solution Leadership & Customer Value**

* Acted as **primary technical authority** translating construction, fabrication, and executive business objectives into Autodesk-centric workflows.
* Led **solution discovery, requirements definition, and technical roadmapping** across design, manufacturing, and construction stakeholders.
* Built **technical business cases** demonstrating cost, schedule, and labor savings from BIM-to-manufacturing automation.

**Autodesk Platform & Construction Technology**

* Designed and implemented **Revit–Inventor data exchange workflows** using Autodesk Data Exchange to support prefabrication and manufacturing.
* Piloted **Autodesk Construction Cloud and Autodesk Platform Services (Forge)** for model interaction, analytics, and interoperability.
* Developed **enterprise-scale Revit automation tools (pyRevit)** to standardize modeling, fabrication readiness, and data integrity.

**Account Strategy & Executive Engagement**

* Partnered with company leadership to evaluate **build / buy / partner** decisions for software platforms and integrations.
* Translated complex technical systems into **clear executive messaging**, enabling informed investment decisions and accelerated adoption.
* Delivered **executive-level dashboards (Power BI)** integrating BIM and ERP data to quantify operational performance and ROI.

**ERP, Analytics & Integration**

* Co-led **Odoo ERP implementation**, including custom modules aligned to AEC workflows.
* Connected ERP, BIM, and fabrication data to support estimating, scheduling, and manufacturing coordination.
* Supported KPI-driven decision making across preconstruction and operations.

**Innovation & Industry Collaboration**

* Early adopter of **Leica iCON robotic layout and laser-scanning workflows**.
* Collaborated directly with Leica Geosystems product teams, providing feedback that influenced hardware and software improvements.
* Represented internal users in vendor discussions, advocating for customer-driven product enhancements.

